The paper discusses a sampling theorem for the acquisition of ensembles of correlated signals, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT). The reconstruction of the ensemble is recast as a low-rank matrix recovery problem, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of random projections, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT) as well as in sparse recovery (cs.SI).
